sidebyside.p:
 Using Gauss's law for a spherical surface with radius r between plates, we get

	E = \begin{cases}
		0 \amp r \lt R_1\\
		\dfrac{1}{4\pi\epsilon_0}\, \dfrac{Q}{r^2} \amp R_1 \lt r \lt R_2\\
		0 \amp r \gt R_2
		\end{cases}

solution.p:
 (a)
				From the formula we evaluate 

					 C \amp = 4\pi\epsilon_0\, \left( \dfrac{1}{R_1} - \dfrac{1}{R_\text{out}} \right)^{-1}
					 \amp = 4\pi\times 8.85\times 10^{-12}\, \left( \dfrac{1}{0.01} - \dfrac{1}{R_\text{0.02}} \right)^{-1}
					 \amp = 4\pi\times 8.85\times 10^{-12}\, \dfrac{0.01\times 0.02}{0.01+0.02} 
					 \amp =  7.4\times 10^{-13}\text{ F}.
